main event: Radar contact of unidentified objects over Dallas, Texas, observed intermittently for 30 minutes without visual confirmation.
interesting points: Objects were detected on AN/APS-13 radar at altitudes of 15,000 ft descending to 40,000 ft before disappearing from the scope,The report suggests the phenomenon may have been intelligently guided,Ground radar operators failed to visually identify the objects despite radar tracking,Conditions were clear with no other air traffic reported in the Dallas area during the sighting,The sighting culminated in recommendation for further radar analysis by ATIC.
sighted object: unidentified aerial objects detected by radar
witness description: No visual sightings made; only radar contacts reported.
